"use strict";(self.webpackChunkbook=self.webpackChunkbook||[]).push([[567],{5226:e=>{e.exports=JSON.parse('{"version":{"pluginId":"default","version":"current","label":"Next","banner":null,"badge":false,"noIndex":false,"className":"docs-version-current","isLast":true,"docsSidebars":{"tutorialSidebar":[{"type":"link","href":"/chapter-1","label":"Chapter 1: Introduction to Physical AI & Humanoid Robotics","docId":"chapter-1","unlisted":false},{"type":"link","href":"/chapter-10","label":"Chapter 10: Advanced Control Systems","docId":"chapter-10","unlisted":false},{"type":"link","href":"/chapter-11","label":"Chapter 11: Sensing and Actuation","docId":"chapter-11","unlisted":false},{"type":"link","href":"/chapter-12","label":"Chapter 12: Robot Kinematics and Dynamics","docId":"chapter-12","unlisted":false},{"type":"link","href":"/chapter-13","label":"Chapter 13: Robot Programming and Software Frameworks","docId":"chapter-13","unlisted":false},{"type":"link","href":"/chapter-14","label":"Chapter 14: Applications of Humanoid Robotics","docId":"chapter-14","unlisted":false},{"type":"link","href":"/chapter-15","label":"Chapter 15: Future Trends and Challenges","docId":"chapter-15","unlisted":false},{"type":"link","href":"/chapter-16","label":"Chapter 16: Building Your Own Humanoid Robot (Project)","docId":"chapter-16","unlisted":false},{"type":"link","href":"/chapter-17","label":"Chapter 17: Conclusion and Outlook","docId":"chapter-17","unlisted":false},{"type":"link","href":"/chapter-2","label":"Chapter 2: Foundations of Robotics","docId":"chapter-2","unlisted":false},{"type":"link","href":"/chapter-3","label":"Chapter 3: Artificial Intelligence in Robotics","docId":"chapter-3","unlisted":false},{"type":"link","href":"/chapter-4","label":"Chapter 4: Perception Systems","docId":"chapter-4","unlisted":false},{"type":"link","href":"/chapter-5","label":"Chapter 5: Manipulation and Grasping","docId":"chapter-5","unlisted":false},{"type":"link","href":"/chapter-6","label":"Chapter 6: Locomotion and Navigation","docId":"chapter-6","unlisted":false},{"type":"link","href":"/chapter-7","label":"Chapter 7: Human-Robot Interaction","docId":"chapter-7","unlisted":false},{"type":"link","href":"/chapter-8","label":"Chapter 8: Learning and Adaptation","docId":"chapter-8","unlisted":false},{"type":"link","href":"/chapter-9","label":"Chapter 9: Ethical Considerations in AI and Robotics","docId":"chapter-9","unlisted":false},{"type":"link","href":"/intro","label":"Introduction","docId":"intro","unlisted":false}]},"docs":{"chapter-1":{"id":"chapter-1","title":"Chapter 1: Introduction to Physical AI & Humanoid Robotics","description":"Welcome to the exciting world of Physical AI and Humanoid Robotics. This book aims to provide a comprehensive understanding of the interdisciplinary field that combines artificial intelligence, robotics, and advanced materials science to create intelligent physical systems capable of interacting with the real world.","sidebar":"tutorialSidebar"},"chapter-10":{"id":"chapter-10","title":"Chapter 10: Advanced Control Systems","description":"The intelligence and physical capabilities of a robot, particularly a humanoid one, are ultimately realized through its control systems. While earlier chapters touched upon the basics of actuation and motion planning, this chapter delves into the advanced control strategies that enable robots to perform complex, dynamic, and precise movements, adapt to disturbances, and interact skillfully with their environment.","sidebar":"tutorialSidebar"},"chapter-11":{"id":"chapter-11","title":"Chapter 11: Sensing and Actuation","description":"While earlier chapters explored the intelligent capabilities of Physical AI and the sophisticated algorithms governing robotic behavior, these would be impossible without the underlying hardware: the sensors that perceive the world and the actuators that enable physical action. This chapter delves deeper into the technologies behind sensing and actuation, crucial components that bridge the digital intelligence with the physical reality of humanoid robotics.","sidebar":"tutorialSidebar"},"chapter-12":{"id":"chapter-12","title":"Chapter 12: Robot Kinematics and Dynamics","description":"To precisely control a robot, especially one with a complex multi-jointed structure like a humanoid, a deep understanding of its motion capabilities is essential. This chapter delves into the mathematical foundations of robot motion: kinematics and dynamics. These concepts provide the tools to describe, analyze, and predict how a robot moves and how forces and torques influence that movement.","sidebar":"tutorialSidebar"},"chapter-13":{"id":"chapter-13","title":"Chapter 13: Robot Programming and Software Frameworks","description":"Bringing the theoretical concepts of Physical AI, kinematics, and dynamics to life in a functional robot requires powerful programming tools and well-structured software frameworks. This chapter explores the common languages, libraries, and operating systems that form the backbone of modern robotics development, enabling engineers and researchers to design, implement, and deploy complex robotic behaviors.","sidebar":"tutorialSidebar"},"chapter-14":{"id":"chapter-14","title":"Chapter 14: Applications of Humanoid Robotics","description":"Having delved into the theoretical foundations, AI integration, hardware components, and software frameworks that enable humanoid robotics, this chapter shifts focus to the practical applications where these advanced Physical AI systems are making a tangible impact. Humanoid robots are uniquely positioned to operate in environments designed for humans, making them ideal candidates for a diverse range of tasks across various sectors.","sidebar":"tutorialSidebar"},"chapter-15":{"id":"chapter-15","title":"Chapter 15: Future Trends and Challenges","description":"The field of Physical AI and humanoid robotics is dynamic, marked by rapid advancements and persistent challenges. As we look towards the future, it\'s clear that these intelligent machines will play an increasingly prominent role in society. This chapter explores the key emerging trends that will shape their development and the significant challenges that must be overcome to realize their full potential.","sidebar":"tutorialSidebar"},"chapter-16":{"id":"chapter-16","title":"Chapter 16: Building Your Own Humanoid Robot (Project)","description":"After exploring the theoretical and practical aspects of Physical AI and humanoid robotics, this chapter provides a hands-on guide to initiating your own humanoid robot project. While building a fully functional, sophisticated humanoid like those discussed in previous chapters is a monumental task, this section will guide you through building a simplified, educational humanoid or a component thereof, focusing on key principles and accessible technologies.","sidebar":"tutorialSidebar"},"chapter-17":{"id":"chapter-17","title":"Chapter 17: Conclusion and Outlook","description":"We have journeyed through the intricate and fascinating world of Physical AI and humanoid robotics, exploring its foundational principles, advanced concepts, and myriad applications. From the basic components that constitute a robot to the sophisticated AI algorithms that imbue them with intelligence, and from the mathematical precision of kinematics to the ethical dilemmas of their integration into society, this book has aimed to provide a comprehensive overview of this rapidly evolving field.","sidebar":"tutorialSidebar"},"chapter-2":{"id":"chapter-2","title":"Chapter 2: Foundations of Robotics","description":"Building upon the introduction to Physical AI and Humanoid Robotics, this chapter delves into the fundamental principles that underpin the field of robotics. Understanding these foundations is crucial for appreciating the complexities and capabilities of modern robots, especially those designed to mimic human characteristics.","sidebar":"tutorialSidebar"},"chapter-3":{"id":"chapter-3","title":"Chapter 3: Artificial Intelligence in Robotics","description":"Having established the fundamental components and disciplines of robotics, we now turn our attention to the pivotal role of Artificial Intelligence (AI) in transforming robots from mere machines into intelligent, autonomous agents. AI is the brain that empowers robots to perceive, reason, learn, and interact with complex, unpredictable environments, a crucial aspect for Physical AI and humanoid robotics.","sidebar":"tutorialSidebar"},"chapter-4":{"id":"chapter-4","title":"Chapter 4: Perception Systems","description":"In the journey of transforming robots into intelligent agents capable of interacting with the physical world, robust perception systems are paramount. Just as humans rely on their senses to understand and navigate their environment, robots depend on a suite of sensors and advanced processing techniques to acquire, interpret, and make sense of the world around them. This chapter delves into the core components and methodologies of robotic perception.","sidebar":"tutorialSidebar"},"chapter-5":{"id":"chapter-5","title":"Chapter 5: Manipulation and Grasping","description":"With an understanding of how robots perceive their environment, we now delve into one of the most critical aspects of physical interaction for humanoid robots: manipulation and grasping. This involves not only moving objects but also understanding their properties, applying appropriate forces, and adapting to unexpected situations. Dexterous manipulation is a hallmark of human intelligence and a significant challenge for robotics.","sidebar":"tutorialSidebar"},"chapter-6":{"id":"chapter-6","title":"Chapter 6: Locomotion and Navigation","description":"Having explored how robots perceive and manipulate objects, we now turn our attention to how they move through and understand their environment: locomotion and navigation. For humanoid robots, emulating human-like mobility is a core design goal, presenting unique challenges compared to wheeled or tracked platforms.","sidebar":"tutorialSidebar"},"chapter-7":{"id":"chapter-7","title":"Chapter 7: Human-Robot Interaction","description":"As robots become more sophisticated and integrate into our daily lives, homes, and workplaces, the nature of their interaction with humans becomes paramount. Human-Robot Interaction (HRI) is a multidisciplinary field focused on understanding, designing, and evaluating robotic systems for use by or with humans. For Physical AI and humanoid robotics, effective HRI is not just a convenience but a necessity for seamless and safe integration.","sidebar":"tutorialSidebar"},"chapter-8":{"id":"chapter-8","title":"Chapter 8: Learning and Adaptation","description":"The ability to learn from experience and adapt to novel situations is a hallmark of intelligence, and for Physical AI and humanoid robotics, it is crucial for achieving true autonomy and versatility. Robots that can learn are not confined to pre-programmed tasks but can improve their performance, acquire new skills, and adjust to dynamic and unpredictable environments. This chapter explores the core mechanisms of robotic learning and adaptation.","sidebar":"tutorialSidebar"},"chapter-9":{"id":"chapter-9","title":"Chapter 9: Ethical Considerations in AI and Robotics","description":"As Physical AI and humanoid robotics advance, their capabilities extend beyond mere task execution to intricate interactions with human society. This brings forth a critical need to address the ethical implications of designing, deploying, and integrating these intelligent systems. This chapter explores the key ethical considerations that researchers, developers, policymakers, and the public must grapple with to ensure a responsible and beneficial future for AI and robotics.","sidebar":"tutorialSidebar"},"intro":{"id":"intro","title":"Introduction","description":"This is the introduction to my book.","sidebar":"tutorialSidebar"}}}}')}}]);